      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. When you say \"modern,\" are you referring to specific types of development? Like, does a society need to follow a certain trajectory—maybe something like the industrialization seen in Europe—to be considered a \"civilization\" in this context? Or do some other cultures fit that definition differently?",
